---
import Layout from '~/layouts/layout.astro';
import Header from '~/components/header.astro';
import Footer from '~/components/footer.astro';

const entry = {
    date: "30 June 2025",
    title: "Midnight Thoughts",
    readTime: "3 min read",
    color: "blue" as const,
    slug: "midnight-thoughts"
};
---

<Layout title="thefuckisthis" description="diary number two.">
    <Header currentPage="entries" />
    
    <main class="pt-20 min-h-screen bg-black">
        <!-- entry header -->
        <section class="py-16 bg-black">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl">
                <!-- back button -->
                <div class="mb-8">
                    <a href="/entries" class="inline-flex items-center text-gray-400 hover:text-white transition-colors group">
                        <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2 transform group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 16l-4-4m0 0l4-4m-4 4h18"></path>
                        </svg>
                        back to entries
                    </a>
                </div>
                
                <!-- entry meta -->
                <div class="text-center mb-12">
                    <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">
                        <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z"></path>
                            </svg>
                            {entry.date}
                        </span>
                        <span>â€¢</span>
                        <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
                            </svg>
                            {entry.readTime}
                        </span>
                    </div>
                    
                    <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-display font-bold mb-6 gradient-text">
                        {entry.title}
                    </h1>
                    
                    <!-- color indicator -->
                    <div class="flex justify-center mb-8">
                        <div class={`w-3 h-3 rounded-full ${entry.color === 'blue' ? 'bg-blue-500' : entry.color === 'green' ? 'bg-green-500' : 'bg-purple-500'}`}></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- entry content -->
        <section class="py-16 bg-black">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-3xl">
                <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
                    <div class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
                        <p class="text-xl text-gray-200 font-light italic border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-6 py-2 bg-green-500/8">
                            Glass Animals said late nights in the middle of June, but I had my thoughts in late June, which was kinda weird. And that got me thinking why does Indie lyrics never relates to us?
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>
                            Everybody knows about that hit song called "Heatwaves" by Glass Animals, and I got to say it is a fucking banger. And everybody knows about the infamous lyric: <i>"Late nights in the middle of June~"</i>
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>
                            And I haven't talked to her for awhile, if the lyrics said in late June it would actually relates to my situation right now, kind of ironic huh?
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>
                            Except at the moment I'm not really thinking about her at all. I'm currently thinking about the future in Software Engineering, you know I spent 2 months learning JavaScript frameworks such as Astro and React. If Web Development dies then it would be a really bummer for me, I invested so much time in learning this part of my life.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>
                            And if we're talking future, we're talking about AI. I got thousands of ideas that I want to test with open-source LLMs, some of it itself is a million dollar idea if successful.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>
                            Currently Anthropic is testing on using its LLM called Claudius to run a retail store, current ongoing results is that Claudius is destroying Anthropic vending machine which is really funny LOL.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>
                            I couldn't help but imagine of making a similar or even the same test in my school but with open source LLMs like Gemma or LLaMA. But if we're being brutally honest, that idea won't go past review and would be immediately declined.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>
                            Making a generic SaaS products isn't the current wave of future in Software Engineering business. AI and LLMs are the future of SaaS, and that is just undeniable facts.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>
                            I used to look down at myself for not utilizing the tools I have to build stuffs. I've changed for good, utilized a simple laptop to build amazing projects.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            Now I'm at the point where I want to level up my game by making my own LLM, but let's be honest that would never happen in a lifetime.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p class="text-gray-400 italic border-l-4 border-gray-600 pl-6 py-2 bg-gray-600/20">
                            I wish I could become like Zuckerberg, but at this rate, it looks like I'll end up as Sohar Parekh.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- navigation -->
        <section class="py-16 bg-black">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl">
                <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-8">
                    <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                        <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-2">Previous Entry</h3>
                        <a href="/entries/first-date" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors">
                            First Date
                        </a>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">30 June 2025</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="text-center">
                        <a href="/entries" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-gray-800 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-700 transition-colors border border-gray-700">
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 11H5m14 0l-4-4m4 4l-4 4"></path>
                            </svg>
                            All Entries
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                        <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-2">Next Entry</h3>
                        <a href="/entries/a-weird-friday" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 transition-colors">
                            A Weird Friday
                        </a>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">4 July 2025</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- related entries -->
        <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-b from-black to-gray-900">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-display font-bold text-white mb-8 text-center">
                    more from the diary
                </h2>
                
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <!-- related entry 1 -->
                    <a href="/entries/first-date" class="group block">
                        <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-700 hover:border-gray-600 transition-all duration-200 group-hover:transform group-hover:scale-105">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                                <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-blue-500"></div>
                                <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">30 June 2025</span>
                            </div>
                            <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-2 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">
                                First Date
                            </h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                Went to a date with this girl that I've always liked. Decided to rekindle the old flame we had...
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                    
                    <!-- related entry 2 -->
                    <a href="/entries/a-weird-friday" class="group block">
                        <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-700 hover:border-gray-600 transition-all duration-200 group-hover:transform group-hover:scale-105">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                                <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500"></div>
                                <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">12 May 2025</span>
                            </div>
                            <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-2 group-hover:text-purple-400 transition-colors">
                                A Weird Friday
                            </h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">
                                Today is Friday, so as a Muslim I went to the mosque to pray with my friends. After prayer...
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
    
    <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
    .prose {
        color: #D1D5DB;
    }
    
    .prose p {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
    }
    
    .prose p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
</style>

<script>
    // smooth scrolling for anchor links
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
        const links = document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]');
        
        links.forEach(link => {
            link.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
                e.preventDefault();
                
                const targetId = this.getAttribute('href').substring(1);
                const targetElement = document.getElementById(targetId);
                
                if (targetElement) {
                    targetElement.scrollIntoView({
                        behavior: 'smooth',
                        block: 'start'
                    });
                }
            });
        });
    });
    
    // reading progress indicator
    function addReadingProgress() {
        const progressBar = document.createElement('div');
        progressBar.className = 'fixed top-0 left-0 h-1 bg-green-500 z-50 transition-all duration-150';
        progressBar.style.width = '0%';
        document.body.appendChild(progressBar);
        
        function updateProgress() {
            const scrollTop = window.pageYOffset;
            const docHeight = document.body.offsetHeight;
            const winHeight = window.innerHeight;
            const scrollPercent = scrollTop / (docHeight - winHeight);
            const scrollPercentRounded = Math.round(scrollPercent * 100);
            
            progressBar.style.width = scrollPercentRounded + '%';
        }
        
        window.addEventListener('scroll', updateProgress);
        updateProgress();
    }
    
    // initialize reading progress
    if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', addReadingProgress);
    } else {
        addReadingProgress();
    }
</script>